info.author: Pepijn de Vos
info.description: # Pyttoresque A Python library for working with NyanCAD tools. * `pyttoresque.netlist`: downloading schematics from a Mosaic CouchDB and generating SPICE netlists. * `pyttoresque.simserver`: simulate netlists on a simulation server and stream results. * `pyttoresque.app`: a Jupyter server extension to host Mosaic and Bokeh on Jupyter https://nyancad.github.io/Mosaic/ This project was funded through the NGI0 PET Fund, a fund established by NLnet with financial support from the European Commission's Next Generation Internet programme, under the aegis of DG Communications Networks, Content and Technology under grant agreement No 825310.
info.name: Pyttoresque
info.summary: Library for working with NyanCAD tools
